1
00:00:09,291 --> 00:00:10,750
That's Kirihito for you.

2
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:11,875
Always has a plan.

3
00:00:11,958 --> 00:00:13,250
Here it is.

4
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:15,541
The Shibakiyama Stable!

5
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:17,041
Home of top-ranked pros

6
00:00:17,125 --> 00:00:19,208
and renowned
for its intense practices!

7
00:00:22,875 --> 00:00:25,541
My first stop in conquering
the pro sumo world.

8
00:00:26,583 --> 00:00:28,375
Ready or not, here I come!

9
00:01:59,791 --> 00:02:01,875
All right!
Keep things moving along!

10
00:02:01,958 --> 00:02:03,333
[BOTH grunting]

11
00:02:03,416 --> 00:02:05,333
[WRESTLERS grunting]

12
00:02:06,416 --> 00:02:08,208
[SAKI]
They're so intense.

13
00:02:08,291 --> 00:02:10,291
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
What're you waiting for? Push!

14
00:02:10,375 --> 00:02:12,916
[SAKI] And Master Shibakiyama
is as sharp-eyed

15
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,458
and intimidating as ever.

16
00:02:14,541 --> 00:02:15,833
Even after retirement.

17
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:20,083
What lovely form but remember
to keep your chin

18
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:22,625
a little bit lower
next time, okay?

19
00:02:22,708 --> 00:02:23,916
[SAKI]
I didn't expect that.

20
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,708
I appreciate you coming
all this way

21
00:02:25,791 --> 00:02:27,583
to watch our training, Saki.

22
00:02:27,666 --> 00:02:28,833
My pleasure.

23
00:02:28,916 --> 00:02:30,541
It's an honor to spend
the next two days

24
00:02:30,625 --> 00:02:31,916
at your stable.

25
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,666
It's weird seeing the master
acting so upbeat.

26
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:36,666
Must be because
we've got company today.

27
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:38,583
Hah! That's for sure.

28
00:02:38,666 --> 00:02:40,583
But I guess you didn't hear
there's another student

29
00:02:40,666 --> 00:02:42,458
stopping by
to have a trial with us.

30
00:02:42,541 --> 00:02:45,166
And apparently, he's some kind
of high school hotshot.

31
00:02:45,250 --> 00:02:46,750
You think we should be worried?

32
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,083
[SHIBAKIYAMA groaning]

33
00:02:48,166 --> 00:02:49,708
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
He should've arrived by now!

34
00:02:49,791 --> 00:02:51,666
I can personally vouch
for his skill

35
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:53,250
and guarantee you
one day he'll be

36
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:55,416
the top-ranked sumo wrestler.

37
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,375
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
A sekitori in the making.

38
00:02:57,458 --> 00:02:59,416
I want him for my stable.

39
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,458
[TERAHARA] Master.
He's coming this way.

40
00:03:01,541 --> 00:03:02,625
Oh! It's about time!

41
00:03:02,708 --> 00:03:05,250
♪

42
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:06,291
-Hmm?
-[growling]

43
00:03:06,375 --> 00:03:08,583
I'm so sorry about being late!

44
00:03:08,666 --> 00:03:10,666
I got turned around
on my way here.

45
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:13,166
Oh, and thanks again for
letting me train with you today.

46
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:16,208
♪

47
00:03:16,291 --> 00:03:18,958
I get it. You're like
his assistant, right?

48
00:03:19,041 --> 00:03:21,916
So, is Ushio waiting for you
to announce him?

49
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,416
[HINOMARU]
Huh? No.

50
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:26,000
I'm Hinomaru Ushio
from the Odachi High sumo club.

51
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:27,833
Do I know him?

52
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:30,000
No, there must be some mistake!

53
00:03:30,083 --> 00:03:31,625
-No.
-But...

54
00:03:31,708 --> 00:03:34,583
I mean, just how tall
are you, son?

55
00:03:34,666 --> 00:03:36,708
Oh, 152 centimeters, sir.

56
00:03:36,791 --> 00:03:39,208
You can barely even reach
the light switch!

57
00:03:39,291 --> 00:03:40,625
Calm down.

58
00:03:40,708 --> 00:03:43,166
[BOY] The master's spirit took
a total nosedive.

59
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:44,375
Can't blame him.

60
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:46,000
[BOY] Look.
The kid's already here.

61
00:03:46,083 --> 00:03:47,041
Let's humor him.

62
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:48,500
Besides, it's just for one day.

63
00:03:48,583 --> 00:03:51,208
[exhaling forcefully]

64
00:03:51,291 --> 00:03:53,458
Hey, your footwork's not bad.

65
00:03:53,541 --> 00:03:54,750
Ushio, was it?

66
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:56,416
You can call me Terahara.

67
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:59,125
I was a high school sumo
up until recently.

68
00:03:59,208 --> 00:04:01,875
As your predecessor,
I'll be your sparring partner.

69
00:04:01,958 --> 00:04:03,416
Don't hold back, all right?

70
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:04,625
Yes, sir.

71
00:04:07,083 --> 00:04:09,708
[HINOMARU] I stretched, but
I'm still feeling kind of stiff.

72
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:10,625
Is it my nerves?

73
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:13,083
[WRESTLERS grunting]

74
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:18,250
[SAKI] The atmosphere's
definitely mellowed out

75
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:19,916
since Hinomaru showed up.

76
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,750
Everyone's way more relaxed.

77
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,916
[sighs] Geez, I know
we're just sparring,

78
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,500
but these guys could at least
set an example for the kid.

79
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:28,416
They're trying to put on
a show for him.

80
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:31,000
He's a fan of sumo after all.

81
00:04:31,083 --> 00:04:33,250
Might as well let him have
some fun until he leaves.

82
00:04:33,333 --> 00:04:35,291
[BOY 2] If you feel
warmed up enough,

83
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:36,541
then let's step inside the ring.

84
00:04:36,625 --> 00:04:38,625
-Yes, sir.
-Actually, before you start,

85
00:04:38,708 --> 00:04:40,333
you want to try your luck
at a little competition

86
00:04:40,416 --> 00:04:41,458
-we're throwing?
-Hmm?

87
00:04:41,541 --> 00:04:43,083
[BOY 2]
Every kid who shows up

88
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:44,791
to one of our practices
gets a shot.

89
00:04:46,083 --> 00:04:48,416
We call it the "Shibakiyama
Knock 'em Out Challenge."

90
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,083
You push one of us
out of the ring,

91
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:52,000
guess what you
could take home with you.

92
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:54,416
That's right,
official stable merchandise!

93
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,875
Whoa!

94
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:58,041
You wanna show the kid
what you've got, Terahara?

95
00:04:58,125 --> 00:04:58,916
Oh, yeah!

96
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,916
♪

97
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,500
[BOY laughs]

98
00:05:02,583 --> 00:05:04,291
Talk about a size difference.

99
00:05:04,375 --> 00:05:05,958
Just do the best you can, Ushio!

100
00:05:06,041 --> 00:05:07,666
[TERAHARA]
Don't worry, kid.

101
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:09,541
You won't go home empty-handed.

102
00:05:09,625 --> 00:05:12,375
I'll step out of the ring
after you've struggled a bit.

103
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:16,333
Hmm.

104
00:05:17,291 --> 00:05:18,208
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
Tera.

105
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:21,541
I recommend
you take this seriously.

106
00:05:23,958 --> 00:05:25,375
Right. Sir.

107
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:27,333
Here I come.

108
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:32,750
[straining]

109
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:33,708
[ALL gasp]

110
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:34,875
He's only a kid.

111
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:36,625
-[BOTH gasp]
-[TERAHARA straining]

112
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:39,458
-[HINOMARU yelling]
-[TERAHARA groans]

113
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,916
[HINOMARU]
Even though I'll never turn down

114
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,916
Shibakiyama Stable merch,

115
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,583
my sumo team needs me
to bring home

116
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:47,666
more than just souvenirs
from this trip.

117
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:49,291
♪

118
00:05:49,375 --> 00:05:50,958
The thing I really want

119
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:53,125
is a full-blown
Shibakiyama session.

120
00:05:55,166 --> 00:05:56,041
[chuckles]

121
00:05:56,125 --> 00:05:57,791
♪

122
00:05:57,875 --> 00:05:58,958
[KEI]
Hinomaru should be training

123
00:05:59,041 --> 00:06:00,500
with top-notch sumo wrestlers

124
00:06:00,583 --> 00:06:01,666
right about now.

125
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:02,916
Hard to believe.

126
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,458
At the Shibakiyama Stable,
that right?

127
00:06:04,541 --> 00:06:06,166
Yeah. And speaking of which,

128
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:07,583
why'd you choose
that one, Coach?

129
00:06:07,666 --> 00:06:09,041
Even among the pros,

130
00:06:09,125 --> 00:06:10,916
they're renowned
for their training.

131
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,625
Before he retired,
the stable master was famous

132
00:06:13,708 --> 00:06:15,416
for his tough practice sessions.

133
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:19,625
The man wasn't exactly blessed
with a godlike physique.

134
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:21,500
What he had
were fearsome attacks,

135
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,625
which earned him
the nickname "Firecracker."

136
00:06:23,708 --> 00:06:26,708
In his prime, he even gave
Yamatokuni a run for his money.

137
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:31,125
Despite his small stature,
he fought head-on.

138
00:06:31,208 --> 00:06:33,208
Additionally,
throughout his career,

139
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:35,500
the man never altered
his charge.

140
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:37,166
Remind you of anyone we know?

141
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:38,583
Yeah.

142
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:39,958
[KIRIHITO] I want to hear
what the master thinks

143
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:41,541
after watching Hinomaru fight.

144
00:06:41,625 --> 00:06:43,916
And there's also
another sumo wrestler there

145
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,666
I'm hoping he'll get
the chance to meet.

146
00:06:47,666 --> 00:06:50,125
[panting]

147
00:06:50,208 --> 00:06:51,750
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
This stable has a reputation

148
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:53,125
for its intense training,

149
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:55,541
especially when I was
at the top of my game.

150
00:06:55,625 --> 00:06:58,708
Even so, many complained
about the regimen and left.

151
00:06:59,666 --> 00:07:01,958
Here I was thinking you were
like those other boys.

152
00:07:02,041 --> 00:07:05,125
Head full of dreams
and a heart with zero ambition.

153
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,416
[HINOMARU grunts]

154
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,583
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
I admit, I misjudged you.

155
00:07:10,666 --> 00:07:13,750
Accept my apologies,
Hinomaru Ushio.

156
00:07:14,708 --> 00:07:16,791
The pro league won't permit
someone of your height.

157
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:20,208
Yet you're besting
sandanme-division wrestlers.

158
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:22,791
He's too much for you to handle?
Then stand back.

159
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:24,083
[HINOMARU grunts]

160
00:07:25,083 --> 00:07:26,875
[SHIBAKIYAMA] Sometimes when
you grab a mawashi belt,

161
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:28,750
your technique shows cracks.

162
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:30,791
-A move, maybe?
-[HINOMARU panting]

163
00:07:30,875 --> 00:07:32,083
No, I have
a more important question.

164
00:07:32,166 --> 00:07:33,625
Let's go, one more time!

165
00:07:33,708 --> 00:07:35,500
[SHIBAKIYAMA] What is that gleam
you have in your eyes?

166
00:07:35,583 --> 00:07:37,416
Yeah! Bring it!

167
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:40,416
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
His enthusiasm is infectious.

168
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,791
It's completely shifted
the mood.

169
00:07:42,875 --> 00:07:45,625
Impressive someone so young
is able to do that.

170
00:07:45,708 --> 00:07:47,250
-[door opens]
-[wind gusting]

171
00:07:50,250 --> 00:07:51,500
[gasps]

172
00:07:53,916 --> 00:07:55,166
Mmm.

173
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:58,333
[SAENOYAMA]
Do you know who our guest is?

174
00:07:58,416 --> 00:08:00,166
That's Hinomaru Ushio.

175
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:02,208
He's visiting
for a one-day trial.

176
00:08:02,291 --> 00:08:04,833
[SAENOYAMA] I remember hearing
he was coming.

177
00:08:04,916 --> 00:08:06,666
He's not half-bad.

178
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:07,958
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
Hey, Nori!

179
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:09,916
Quit crouching there
like a creeper.

180
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,333
Get your ass in here.

181
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:15,208
-[door creaks]
-[SAENOYAMA] Forgive me.

182
00:08:15,291 --> 00:08:17,958
It sounded like you were having
such a productive session,

183
00:08:18,041 --> 00:08:20,000
I didn't want to interrupt
and break the momentum.

184
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:24,666
Actually, to tell you the truth,
I couldn't tear my eyes away.

185
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,000
[SAKI]
Uh...

186
00:08:26,083 --> 00:08:28,666
The ninth-ranked maegashira,
Saenoyama!

187
00:08:31,208 --> 00:08:32,833
[ALL WRESTLERS]
Good morning, sekitori!

188
00:08:35,875 --> 00:08:38,041
[SAKI] So far,
Ushio's been fighting trainees

189
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:40,416
from the makushita division
and below.

190
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,458
I-I mean, not to say
they're pushovers,

191
00:08:42,541 --> 00:08:45,125
but they're second
and third-rate pros at best.

192
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:47,458
There are 700
elite sumo wrestlers,

193
00:08:47,541 --> 00:08:50,083
but only 70
in the juryo division and above

194
00:08:50,166 --> 00:08:51,416
are sekitoris

195
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,083
and can tie
their hair in an o-icho topknot.

196
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:56,291
Plus, only they're allowed
to wear a white mawashi belt

197
00:08:56,375 --> 00:08:57,833
during practice.

198
00:08:57,916 --> 00:09:00,166
If you wanted to meet
one of the best, Ushio,

199
00:09:00,250 --> 00:09:01,291
here he is.

200
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:03,583
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
The boy created a mood

201
00:09:03,666 --> 00:09:05,000
similar to a practice session

202
00:09:05,083 --> 00:09:06,291
for a sekitori.

203
00:09:06,375 --> 00:09:07,458
I wonder.

204
00:09:07,541 --> 00:09:10,041
Now that an actual sekitori
is here,

205
00:09:10,125 --> 00:09:12,291
will things get even more tense?

206
00:09:12,375 --> 00:09:13,291
[SAKI]
Uhh...

207
00:09:13,375 --> 00:09:14,875
[SAENOYAMA]
Good morning.

208
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:16,750
Thank you for your
assistance earlier.

209
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:19,000
[SAKI] No, thank you
for letting me attend.

210
00:09:19,083 --> 00:09:20,708
[SAENOYAMA]
Good morning to you, Master.

211
00:09:20,791 --> 00:09:22,500
-[SHIBAKIYAMA] Hmm.
-Sekitori!

212
00:09:22,583 --> 00:09:24,166
It'd be an honor
to have a bout with you!

213
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:26,041
-[SAKI gasps]
-[SHIBAKIYAMA] Hmm.

214
00:09:26,125 --> 00:09:27,416
Slow down.

215
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:30,166
He only just arrived
at practice, Ushio.

216
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:31,333
[SAENOYAMA]
You read my mind.

217
00:09:31,416 --> 00:09:32,583
I'd also like to duel.

218
00:09:32,666 --> 00:09:34,416
[BOY 3]
Huh! Sekitori?

219
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:36,125
It's uncommon,

220
00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:38,041
but you've piqued my interest.

221
00:09:38,125 --> 00:09:40,375
♪

222
00:09:46,708 --> 00:09:48,583
[HINOMARU] Is this
the opportunity you were hoping

223
00:09:48,666 --> 00:09:49,833
I'd get, Kirihito?

224
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:53,208
Even the weaker fighters
gave me a workout,

225
00:09:53,291 --> 00:09:54,291
but let's be honest.

226
00:09:55,708 --> 00:09:58,416
Kusanagi was on
a completely different level.

227
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:00,750
Ordinary opponents won't do.

228
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:02,833
I need to fight wrestlers
who will challenge me.

229
00:10:03,791 --> 00:10:05,083
Like Saenoyama.

230
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:08,500
[SHIBAKIYAMA] I'll admit,
we underestimated you

231
00:10:08,583 --> 00:10:10,166
when you first walked in.

232
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:11,750
-However...
-Now! Spirit!

233
00:10:14,208 --> 00:10:15,166
[HINOMARU]
He's not moving.

234
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,333
[groans]

235
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:20,291
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
You made the same mistake, boy.

236
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:25,791
[HINOMARU]
I found it.

237
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:30,000
Nice. Can we go
another round?

238
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:31,333
This is what I came for.

239
00:10:31,416 --> 00:10:32,833
[HINOMARU groans]

240
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:35,833
I'm not making any headway.

241
00:10:35,916 --> 00:10:38,333
His legs are so flexible.

242
00:10:38,416 --> 00:10:39,916
My attacks have
no effect on him.

243
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,375
Then in a flash, he turns
his body into a boulder.

244
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:43,833
[groans]

245
00:10:43,916 --> 00:10:45,375
The might of a pro.

246
00:10:45,458 --> 00:10:47,625
"You should be like water."

247
00:10:47,708 --> 00:10:49,541
My master taught me that.

248
00:10:49,625 --> 00:10:51,791
Your form must be
as agile as fluid

249
00:10:51,875 --> 00:10:53,416
and strike
with torrential force.

250
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:55,458
Be like water, huh?

251
00:10:55,541 --> 00:10:57,333
[SAENOYAMA]
Whereas your sumo is like fire,

252
00:10:57,416 --> 00:10:58,875
continuously raging.

253
00:10:58,958 --> 00:11:00,083
You could say it's heroic,

254
00:11:00,166 --> 00:11:01,916
but you might
also call it sloppy.

255
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:04,083
Thank you very much.

256
00:11:05,041 --> 00:11:07,250
I understand the range
of your abilities.

257
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,916
Sekitori, please, wait!

258
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,666
Any further bouts would be
a waste of both our time.

259
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:15,083
I've one duty, and that's
achieve the rank of yokozuna.

260
00:11:15,166 --> 00:11:18,666
A glory my master was unable
to reach during his career.

261
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:20,416
[HINOMARU]
But I'm only here today.

262
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,333
Please, just one more bout!

263
00:11:22,416 --> 00:11:24,083
[SAENOYAMA]
Haven't you had enough?

264
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:26,041
I am at a loss
as to what spurs you on.

265
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,666
Even if you can't best me,
you shouldn't feel ashamed.

266
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:32,500
I don't know a single person
here who'd dare call you weak.

267
00:11:33,708 --> 00:11:36,791
I feel you'll be moderately
successful in high school sumo.

268
00:11:36,875 --> 00:11:39,666
Being moderately successful
isn't good enough for me!

269
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:42,750
I intend to become a yokozuna,
same as you!

270
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:44,666
That's my reason
for not giving up!

271
00:11:44,750 --> 00:11:47,333
♪

272
00:11:47,416 --> 00:11:48,625
[SAENOYAMA]
Like me?

273
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:51,500
Your dream is born
of childish idealism.

274
00:11:51,583 --> 00:11:53,375
Meanwhile, I speak
knowing full well

275
00:11:53,458 --> 00:11:55,916
how long and arduous
the road actually is.

276
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,500
And you think we're the same?

277
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:59,833
♪

278
00:11:59,916 --> 00:12:01,625
You requested one more bout.

279
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:02,958
Very well.

280
00:12:03,041 --> 00:12:04,333
Maybe you think
you'll have a growth spurt

281
00:12:04,416 --> 00:12:06,500
or your luck
will suddenly change.

282
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:08,208
But I'm warning you now.

283
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:10,958
Your words were an insult
to sumo wrestlers,

284
00:12:11,041 --> 00:12:13,166
and I'll make you pay
dearly for it.

285
00:12:18,375 --> 00:12:20,875
That expression.
He means business.

286
00:12:20,958 --> 00:12:22,333
[HINOMARU]
Don't back down.

287
00:12:22,416 --> 00:12:24,125
This is exactly why I'm here.

288
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:26,541
It's my last chance
of finding a way to evolve.

289
00:12:27,541 --> 00:12:29,500
I need to do something different
with my charge.

290
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,875
Gotta be realistic.

291
00:12:31,958 --> 00:12:34,083
I don't have the skill yet
to overpower a sekitori.

292
00:12:34,166 --> 00:12:36,458
But I'm out of options.

293
00:12:36,541 --> 00:12:38,916
I'll go low
and fast as possible!

294
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,625
He's in a spider stance.

295
00:12:40,708 --> 00:12:43,125
Keep experimenting
till you find what works.

296
00:12:43,208 --> 00:12:45,625
♪

297
00:12:45,708 --> 00:12:46,708
Now! Spirit!

298
00:12:46,791 --> 00:12:49,208
♪

299
00:12:49,291 --> 00:12:50,750
[SAENOYAMA yells]

300
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:51,625
[grunts]

301
00:12:51,708 --> 00:12:53,000
[TERAHARA]
Oh, man!

302
00:12:53,083 --> 00:12:55,041
Side slaps are banned
in amateur competitions.

303
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:57,791
♪

304
00:12:57,875 --> 00:12:58,916
[SAENOYAMA]
Interesting.

305
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,458
He used his knees as a cushion

306
00:13:00,541 --> 00:13:01,916
to absorb the impact.

307
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,750
[HINOMARU]
After all my previous bouts,

308
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:05,083
I don't have much strength left.

309
00:13:06,041 --> 00:13:07,375
I've got to be like water.

310
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:09,583
Fluidity varies your rhythm

311
00:13:09,666 --> 00:13:11,125
and dictates the tempo
in a bout.

312
00:13:11,208 --> 00:13:14,916
But you forgot,
fire doesn't just rage.

313
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,208
It flickers and burns!

314
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:18,583
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
This is it.

315
00:13:18,666 --> 00:13:20,458
This is what you came
to my stable to find.

316
00:13:20,541 --> 00:13:22,333
[HINOMARU] Kirihito went
through the trouble

317
00:13:22,416 --> 00:13:24,875
of finding me
a damn good sparring partner.

318
00:13:24,958 --> 00:13:26,458
I can't waste this opportunity!

319
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:31,166
If I'm reaching the top,
it means devouring you!

320
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:34,166
[SAENOYAMA] Some
incredible force is erupting

321
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:35,083
from within him!

322
00:13:35,166 --> 00:13:38,250
[roaring]

323
00:13:41,916 --> 00:13:44,041
[BOTH yell]

324
00:13:44,125 --> 00:13:45,791
-[thud]
-[BOTH gasp]

325
00:13:45,875 --> 00:13:47,416
[ALL gasp]

326
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:51,750
[SAKI]
The sekitori pushed Ushio

327
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:53,208
to the ground first.

328
00:13:53,291 --> 00:13:54,625
But look at his knee.

329
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:55,916
He still went down!

330
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,375
[panting]

331
00:13:58,458 --> 00:14:01,000
[HINOMARU]
My body was moving on its own.

332
00:14:01,083 --> 00:14:02,833
It wasn't the same
as what Kirihito did,

333
00:14:02,916 --> 00:14:04,208
but it felt so natural.

334
00:14:05,166 --> 00:14:07,333
It must've been some kind
of new technique.

335
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:08,833
I almost had it.

336
00:14:08,916 --> 00:14:10,333
I was nearly there.

337
00:14:11,416 --> 00:14:13,208
Damn. Damn!

338
00:14:13,291 --> 00:14:16,250
[SAENOYAMA] As we agreed upon,
that's our final bout.

339
00:14:18,250 --> 00:14:19,791
Thank you for sparring with me.

340
00:14:19,875 --> 00:14:21,833
[SAENOYAMA] I expect to see you
here again tomorrow.

341
00:14:21,916 --> 00:14:24,041
-[gasps]
-Your sumo intrigues me,

342
00:14:24,125 --> 00:14:26,375
and I'd like to see a bit more
of what you can do.

343
00:14:26,458 --> 00:14:29,666
I may not look it,
but I'm a real curious guy.

344
00:14:31,666 --> 00:14:33,166
I'll be here!
Count on it!

345
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:37,958
So, did you have fun
at your remedial class?

346
00:14:38,041 --> 00:14:41,208
Some punk called Gengoro
from Ishigami stopped by.

347
00:14:41,291 --> 00:14:42,416
Gengoro?

348
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:45,000
-[cell phone buzzing]
-Hmm?

349
00:14:45,083 --> 00:14:46,083
Hello?

350
00:14:46,166 --> 00:14:48,125
Uh-huh. Wait.
You're staying?

351
00:14:48,208 --> 00:14:50,375
[HINOMARU]
Saenoyama's already agreed

352
00:14:50,458 --> 00:14:52,458
to spar with me more tomorrow.

353
00:14:52,541 --> 00:14:54,958
So the master said it made sense
if I stayed overnight.

354
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:59,000
Think you'll learn it?
Your new move?

355
00:14:59,083 --> 00:15:00,666
[HINOMARU] I'll let you know
when I see you.

356
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:02,708
-Later.
-[phone beeps]

357
00:15:03,708 --> 00:15:05,000
Was that Hinomaru?

358
00:15:05,083 --> 00:15:06,250
It was.

359
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:07,958
He's spending the night
at the stable.

360
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:10,166
Seems he's training tomorrow
as well.

361
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:12,083
Guess he made
a good first impression.

362
00:15:12,166 --> 00:15:13,416
We have to work hard too.

363
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:14,791
Gotta help him carry the weight.

364
00:15:14,875 --> 00:15:17,083
Good, 'cause that's
my specialty.

365
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:19,083
If you want to help,
don't fail any more tests.

366
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:20,916
I'm a C plus student now!

367
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,791
[KIRIHITO]
They may think you're cheating.

368
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:28,416
Authentic sumo stable
chankonabe stew!

369
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:31,000
Kid! You did good
out there today!

370
00:15:31,083 --> 00:15:32,208
Thanks a lot, sir.

371
00:15:32,291 --> 00:15:34,291
Grab a seat and pour a bowl.

372
00:15:34,375 --> 00:15:35,875
The sekitori's
still eating though.

373
00:15:35,958 --> 00:15:38,041
Today's an exception.
So chow down.

374
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:39,000
Yes, sir!

375
00:15:39,083 --> 00:15:40,125
[SAKI chuckles]

376
00:15:40,208 --> 00:15:41,708
The apprentices
usually eat last,

377
00:15:41,791 --> 00:15:42,916
so you shouldn't feel bad.

378
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,041
I know, but...

379
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:47,875
It's still kinda awkward.

380
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:50,291
[SAENOYAMA] I understand
you're a national treasure,

381
00:15:50,375 --> 00:15:51,583
Onimaru Kunitsuna.

382
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:53,083
Are you serious?

383
00:15:53,166 --> 00:15:54,666
It's not that big of a deal.

384
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:56,500
Why are you being so modest?

385
00:15:56,583 --> 00:15:58,583
I heard you held you own
against Kusanagi.

386
00:15:58,666 --> 00:15:59,958
Wait a minute, who told you?

387
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:02,333
Please. I'm a high school
sumo club manager,

388
00:16:02,416 --> 00:16:05,083
which means gossip
inevitably finds its way to me.

389
00:16:05,166 --> 00:16:07,750
By Kusanagi,
you're referring to...

390
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:11,291
Sosuke Kuze,
a national treasure, yeah.

391
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:15,375
The son of Yamatokuni,
the former yokozuna.

392
00:16:15,458 --> 00:16:16,833
A legend.

393
00:16:16,916 --> 00:16:18,333
There's no way.

394
00:16:18,416 --> 00:16:21,291
He's a popular topic
of discussion these days.

395
00:16:21,375 --> 00:16:22,916
They say he's gonna shoot
through the ranks

396
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,416
if he turns pro.

397
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:27,000
So you are in the same
generation as he is, are ya?

398
00:16:28,166 --> 00:16:29,333
Tough break, kiddo.

399
00:16:30,291 --> 00:16:31,541
[SAENOYAMA]
Who was stronger?

400
00:16:31,625 --> 00:16:32,458
Me or junior?

401
00:16:32,541 --> 00:16:33,500
[gasps]

402
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:39,041
Well, all I know is I did a lot
better fighting against him

403
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:41,125
-than against you.
-[ALL laughing]

404
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:42,791
Yeah, sounds right.

405
00:16:42,875 --> 00:16:44,750
Hey, I don't see
your chopsticks moving.

406
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:46,125
Stew's a three-bowl minimum.

407
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:47,416
[HINOMARU]
Y-yes, sir!

408
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:48,791
[BOY 4] And after
you've eaten your fill,

409
00:16:48,875 --> 00:16:50,083
we snooze.

410
00:16:50,166 --> 00:16:52,166
[snoring]

411
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:55,458
♪

412
00:16:59,041 --> 00:17:00,625
We're off to buy groceries
for dinner.

413
00:17:00,708 --> 00:17:01,958
[HINOMARU]
When you're an apprentice,

414
00:17:02,041 --> 00:17:03,541
there's no shortage
of chores to do.

415
00:17:04,958 --> 00:17:07,125
The thing is, it's a lot of fun.

416
00:17:07,208 --> 00:17:10,083
I know it's not all
about cutting loose.

417
00:17:10,166 --> 00:17:11,708
You're living to compete,
after all.

418
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:14,083
I bet each wrestler has

419
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:16,833
their own private doubts
and anxieties.

420
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:18,625
In fact, I'm sure of it.

421
00:17:18,708 --> 00:17:20,833
For the longest time, I wanted

422
00:17:20,916 --> 00:17:22,375
-to be a part of this...
-[BOY 5] Awesome.

423
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:24,416
[HINOMARU] A member
of the pro sumo world.

424
00:17:25,416 --> 00:17:26,750
I'm not here to goof off.

425
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:29,958
Not when I haven't accomplished
anything yet.

426
00:17:30,041 --> 00:17:32,583
But still, if only
for a short while,

427
00:17:32,666 --> 00:17:36,416
let me soak up this feeling,
until I have to leave.

428
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:39,041
♪

429
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:41,750
[scraping]

430
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:42,791
[moans]

431
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:45,375
[scraping continues]

432
00:17:49,666 --> 00:17:51,333
I didn't mean to wake you up.

433
00:17:51,416 --> 00:17:52,625
Sorry about that.

434
00:17:52,708 --> 00:17:54,833
I couldn't sleep
and decided to run drills.

435
00:17:54,916 --> 00:17:57,291
I wanted to revisit
everything I felt today,

436
00:17:57,375 --> 00:17:58,750
if that makes sense.

437
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,833
You're too excited to rest,
I get it.

438
00:18:00,916 --> 00:18:02,583
I want to be a pro.

439
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:05,625
And spending the day here
only reinvigorated that desire.

440
00:18:06,583 --> 00:18:08,500
[SAKI] On my days off,
I've been arranging to stay

441
00:18:08,583 --> 00:18:10,375
at various sumo stables.

442
00:18:10,458 --> 00:18:13,083
My brother wants to turn pro,
the same as you.

443
00:18:13,166 --> 00:18:14,291
While he's busy practicing,

444
00:18:14,375 --> 00:18:16,000
I've been scoping
them out for him.

445
00:18:16,083 --> 00:18:17,708
Yeah?

446
00:18:17,791 --> 00:18:19,416
[SAKI]
So, tell me the truth.

447
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:20,708
Who was stronger?

448
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:22,500
Saenoyama or Kuze?

449
00:18:26,583 --> 00:18:28,666
Well, obviously,
the sekitori has more power

450
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:30,250
and better technique.

451
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:33,333
And even though I appreciate him
agreeing to spar with me,

452
00:18:33,416 --> 00:18:34,833
truthfully,

453
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:37,125
if they were to fight each other
at this moment,

454
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:38,750
I couldn't say who would win.

455
00:18:39,750 --> 00:18:42,625
Maybe Kuze is looming
in my mind after our bout.

456
00:18:43,583 --> 00:18:45,375
I knew I wanted to fight someone
who'd be similar

457
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:46,833
in height and technique.

458
00:18:46,916 --> 00:18:49,416
If I can't take on
a full-strength sekitori,

459
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:50,791
then I can never...

460
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:52,708
-[SHIBAKIYAMA] Now I understand.
-[switch clicks]

461
00:18:52,791 --> 00:18:55,333
It seems this friend of yours
chose Saenoyama

462
00:18:55,416 --> 00:18:58,000
as a stand-in for training
against Sosuke Kuze.

463
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,333
[HINOMARU]
Master. You're up!

464
00:19:00,416 --> 00:19:02,541
After fighting with
the sekitori yesterday,

465
00:19:02,625 --> 00:19:04,875
I imagine there's plenty
you want to work on.

466
00:19:04,958 --> 00:19:07,750
So, we better start sparring
right away.

467
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:08,750
[HINOMARU]
Huh?

468
00:19:09,708 --> 00:19:11,291
[crowd cheering]

469
00:19:11,375 --> 00:19:13,458
[SHIBAKIYAMA] When everyone said
I was past my prime,

470
00:19:13,541 --> 00:19:16,125
I defeated
the higher-ranked Yamatokuni.

471
00:19:16,208 --> 00:19:19,208
I promise there's still one or
two lessons I could teach you.

472
00:19:20,916 --> 00:19:22,375
What's the matter with you, son?

473
00:19:22,458 --> 00:19:24,875
I don't take my shirt off
for just anybody, you know.

474
00:19:26,041 --> 00:19:27,125
[HINOMARU]
I guess I'm confused

475
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:29,458
why you're invested
in my future.

476
00:19:29,541 --> 00:19:31,375
I'd understand
if I was a sumo wrestler

477
00:19:31,458 --> 00:19:32,500
destined to turn pro.

478
00:19:32,583 --> 00:19:35,083
But I'm a... well...

479
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:39,000
[SHIBAKIYAMA] Chalk it up
to another habit of growing old.

480
00:19:39,083 --> 00:19:41,708
But when I look at you,
I see myself.

481
00:19:41,791 --> 00:19:45,666
In my youth,
I was called small. Helpless.

482
00:19:45,750 --> 00:19:48,541
But I still fought with passion
to become a yokozuna.

483
00:19:48,625 --> 00:19:50,958
I only made it
as high as sekiwake.

484
00:19:51,041 --> 00:19:52,875
And though I was praised
for my accomplishment,

485
00:19:52,958 --> 00:19:54,625
I never achieved
my actual dream.

486
00:19:54,708 --> 00:19:57,583
I passed my ambition
onto Saenoyama

487
00:19:57,666 --> 00:19:59,458
thinking height was
what held me back.

488
00:19:59,541 --> 00:20:02,833
But after watching you,
I have one more dream left.

489
00:20:02,916 --> 00:20:06,250
To see someone our size
become a yokozuna.

490
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:08,000
Realize that dream for me!

491
00:20:08,083 --> 00:20:10,416
♪

492
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,500
That was a bit long-winded,
I admit,

493
00:20:12,583 --> 00:20:14,875
but I'm saying I believe in you.

494
00:20:14,958 --> 00:20:17,000
When you're ready
to turn pro, find me.

495
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:18,750
I'll be waiting for you, kid.

496
00:20:19,791 --> 00:20:21,250
Sir!

497
00:20:21,333 --> 00:20:25,333
What's Hinomaru doing up?
Aah! The master's awake too!

498
00:20:25,416 --> 00:20:26,708
And practicing with him?

499
00:20:26,791 --> 00:20:29,375
Looks like everybody's
too excited to sleep.

500
00:20:29,458 --> 00:20:30,541
[TERAHARA]
Aw, screw it!

501
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:32,000
Let's start practice now!

502
00:20:32,083 --> 00:20:33,583
[ALL STUDENTS cheering]

503
00:20:33,666 --> 00:20:36,333
[SAKI] A high school student
getting the pros stoked.

504
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:39,333
Hinomaru Ushio, huh?

505
00:20:39,416 --> 00:20:41,500
[SAKI]
Thank you for everything.

506
00:20:41,583 --> 00:20:43,708
Man, that was so much fun.

507
00:20:43,791 --> 00:20:45,541
And having someone around
to talk to

508
00:20:45,625 --> 00:20:47,708
who was my own age
made things easier.

509
00:20:47,791 --> 00:20:49,083
Thanks for coming.

510
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:51,166
It was good to meet
a fellow sumo enthusiast.

511
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,916
If both our schools win
enough bouts,

512
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,666
we'll see each other
at nationals.

513
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,166
Well, I can guarantee
I'll be there,

514
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:58,291
since I'm going to become
a high school yokozuna.

515
00:20:58,375 --> 00:21:00,375
I certainly hope you do,

516
00:21:00,458 --> 00:21:02,291
but since my brother's
also competing,

517
00:21:02,375 --> 00:21:04,750
you may have to hold off on
your dream until the next year.

518
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:06,166
Wait.

519
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:07,791
You told me you were
a sumo manager

520
00:21:07,875 --> 00:21:10,083
but never what
high school you go to.

521
00:21:10,166 --> 00:21:11,750
Tottori Hakuro.

522
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:13,333
Tottori Hakuro?

523
00:21:13,416 --> 00:21:14,458
You mean...

524
00:21:15,666 --> 00:21:17,166
I'm Saki Tennoji.

525
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:19,416
Anyway. It was good
to meet you.

526
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:20,875
[gasps]

527
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:24,333
[HINOMARU]
The sister of Shido Tennoji,

528
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:26,000
the national champion!

529
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,375
[SAKI]
I thought Ishigami was sure

530
00:21:28,458 --> 00:21:29,958
to be the winning team
from Chiba,

531
00:21:30,041 --> 00:21:31,875
but I learned something new.

532
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:35,125
All right, Onimaru Kunitsuna
from Odachi High.

533
00:21:36,125 --> 00:21:37,541
Guess I'll see you at the top.

534
00:21:37,625 --> 00:21:38,625
I'll be waiting.

535
00:21:39,583 --> 00:21:43,708
Tennoji, Kuze, and Sada
from Ishigami.

536
00:21:43,791 --> 00:21:44,916
Before I meet them in the ring,

537
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,875
I need to perfect
my new technique,

538
00:21:46,958 --> 00:21:48,416
so I can beat them all!

539
00:23:19,458 --> 00:23:20,500
[laughs]

540
00:23:20,583 --> 00:23:22,333
-Check it out, Yuma.
-So?

541
00:23:22,416 --> 00:23:24,625
Don't act like it's a big deal.
They're for sale.

542
00:23:24,708 --> 00:23:26,833
-[HINOMARU] What do you think?
-Hmm?

543
00:23:26,916 --> 00:23:29,375
The only thing shirts do
is cover up sweet muscles.

544
00:23:29,458 --> 00:23:31,208
-Aww!
-Oh. Hey.

545
00:23:31,291 --> 00:23:33,000
A Shibakiyama T-shirt.

546
00:23:33,083 --> 00:23:35,500
So cool.
I'd love one of those.

547
00:23:35,583 --> 00:23:37,500
-[HINOMARU crying] Captain!
-Huh? Okay.

